history.content: The spring 2021 schedule goes live in less than a week, so you'll be able to see for yourself then. My gut instinct is that you'll be fine though

As the Enrollment Manager for CompSci, I always tell students that how you use your phase 1 units indicates your highest priority choices. If you really MUST get into CS 189, don't wait for phase 2. This class is extremely competitive to get into during SP semesters and in my past experience with Prof Shewchuk, he has prioritized making enough seats for grad students available. (remember, this is a combined class). That said, every semester is a bit different.

You can always check past enrollment history for classes by searching for CS 189 on berkeleytime.com and then decide for yourself your comfort level with waiting for phase 2.

children.subject: last year, things were completely full by the time juniors were done registering IIRC.  Not even waitlist was available.  The original caps were a bit different - 410 for enroll, 400 for waitlist.  Just so you know.

history.content: I'm thinking about Phase 2-ing CS 189 for Spring 2021 enrollment. In this regard, I was wondering if there are reserved seats for EECS/declared LnS CS majors and if it would be possible to avoid the waitlist in phase 2-ing. I do have priority enrollment and will have my phase 2 before most other students so I guess the question reduces to are there reserved seats for EECS/LnS CS majors in CS 189 enrollment and if so, do these reserved seats end up filling by the end of Phase 1? Maybe Prof. Shewchuck can chime in with his experience in previous spring iterations of 189.
